Entire Learning Journey
-----------------------

Step 7 – Backend Integration
Built the Flask backend.
Created /start and /chat APIs.
Connected the OpenAI Assistant API.
Created a Google Cloud project.
Enabled the Google Sheets API.
Created a Service Account and downloaded the JSON key.
Shared the Google Sheet with the Service Account.
Installed required Python packages (gspread, oauth2client, etc.).
Stored chatbot leads in Google Sheets.
Tested the backend successfully.
Step 8 – Deployment
Created the chatbot workflow in Voiceflow.
Connected Voiceflow to the Flask APIs.
Tested the chatbot using Prototype mode.
Published the Voiceflow assistant.
Generated the web widget embed code.
Logged into WordPress.
Added the widget using an HTML block in Elementor.
Updated the page.
Verified that the chatbot appeared and worked on the live website.

In summary: You progressed from a Python backend and AI integration to a fully deployed, production-ready website chatbot. 
The complete solution now connects Voiceflow → Flask → OpenAI Assistant → Google Sheets → WordPress, enabling website visitors to chat with an AI assistant 
while optionally capturing their details in Google Sheets.

